  }), mdx("p", null, "\"Weighted Shortest Job First\" (WSJF) is not really a Lean tool.  It's something used in Agile software development to prioritize work.  I've only learned about this recently, but it does seem quite useful.  The tool is designed to address the biggest trade-off in any project: potential impact versus time to implement.  If you were to list out all the potential improvements your team could make (to your software or your business as a whole), they will likely fall into two categories:"), mdx("ol", null, mdx("li", {
